Exercise 1: Code Readability Improvement (Java)
Original Code
class UserMgr {
    private List<U> u_list;
    private DBConn db;
    public boolean a(String un, String pw, String em) {
        if (un.length() < 3 || pw.length() < 8 || !em.contains('@')) return false;
        for (U user : u_list) {
            if (user.getUn().equals(un)) return false;
        }
        U nu = new U(un, pw, em);
        u_list.add(nu);
        boolean res = db.execute("INSERT INTO users VALUES ('" + un + "', '" + pw + "', '" + em + "')");
        return res;
    }
    public U f(String un) {
        for (U user : u_list) {
            if (user.getUn().equals(un)) return user;
        }
        return null;
    }
}

My Initial Observations
Question	My Answer	What It Actually Means
What does U mean?	I don't know	User — single letter class names are unreadable
What does un mean?	I don't know	username — abbreviated beyond recognition
What does a() do?	I don't know	addUser() — method names must describe their action
How many responsibilities in a()?	Not sure	Three: validate, check duplicate, save to database

